Merge

df_long <- df_p %>%
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  tibble::rownames_to_column("protein") %>%
  tidyr::pivot_longer(
    cols = -protein,
    names_to = "ID",
    values_to = "y"
  )

# Join with meta
df_long <- df_long %>%
  left_join(meta, by = "ID")

Fit model

disease_effects <- df_long %>%
  group_by(protein) %>%
  do({
    fit <- lm(y ~ Diagnosis, data = .)
    tidy(fit) %>%
      filter(term != "(Intercept)") %>%
      select(term, estimate, p.value) %>%
      mutate(comparison = gsub("Diagnosis", "CTRL vs ", term))
  }) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  select(protein, comparison, estimate, p.value)

With imputation

concurrency_scores <- df_long %>%
  group_by(protein) %>%
  group_modify(~ {
    fit <- lmer(y ~ Diagnosis + condition + (1|intern), data = .x)
    vc <- VarCorr(fit)
    sigma_donor <- as.numeric(vc$intern)
    sigma_resid <- attr(vc, "sc")^2
    tibble(concurrency = sigma_donor / (sigma_donor + sigma_resid))
    }) %>%
  ungroup()

Without imputation

# Start from your merged long table (non-imputed)
# intern = donor, condition = region code, Diagnosis = disease
dfn <- df_long %>%
  filter(!is.na(y)) %>%
  mutate(
    region    = factor(condition, levels = c("FC","CER","STR","SN","MED")),
    Diagnosis = factor(Diagnosis),
    intern    = factor(intern)   # donor as random effect
  )

# Helper: for each protein, keep donors that have >=2 observed regions (for that protein)
prepare_for_fit <- function(df_prot) {
  donor_counts <- df_prot %>%
    group_by(intern) %>%
    summarise(n_obs = n(), .groups = "drop")
  df_prot %>%
    inner_join(filter(donor_counts, n_obs >= 2), by = "intern")
}

# Helper: check if the random effect is estimable for this protein
ok_for_lmer <- function(df_prot) {
  n_obs <- nrow(df_prot)
  n_lev <- nlevels(droplevels(df_prot$intern))
  # Need: some donors with repeats AND more obs than donor levels
  has_repeats <- any(table(droplevels(df_prot$intern)) >= 2)
  n_obs > n_lev && has_repeats
}

# Fit one protein safely
fit_one <- function(df_prot) {
  # Drop to donors with >=2 regions for this protein
  dfp <- prepare_for_fit(df_prot)

  # If too sparse after filtering, return NA
  if (!ok_for_lmer(dfp)) return(tibble(concurrency = NA_real_))

  # Build fixed-effect part dynamically to avoid singularities:
  rhs <- c()
  if (n_distinct(dfp$Diagnosis) > 1) rhs <- c(rhs, "Diagnosis")
  if (n_distinct(dfp$region)    > 1) rhs <- c(rhs, "region")
  fixed <- if (length(rhs)) paste(rhs, collapse = " + ") else "1"

  fmla <- as.formula(paste0("y ~ ", fixed, " + (1|intern)"))

  fit <- try(lmer(fmla, data = dfp, REML = TRUE), silent = TRUE)
  if (inherits(fit, "try-error")) return(tibble(concurrency = NA_real_))

  vc <- VarCorr(fit)
  if (!("intern" %in% names(vc))) return(tibble(concurrency = NA_real_))

  sigma_donor <- as.numeric(vc$intern)
  sigma_resid <- attr(vc, "sc")^2
  tibble(concurrency = sigma_donor / (sigma_donor + sigma_resid))
}

concurrency_scores <- dfn %>%
  group_by(protein) %>%
  group_modify(~ fit_one(.x)) %>%
  ungroup()

Merge

merged <- disease_effects %>%
  left_join(concurrency_scores, by = "protein")

Downstream with imputation

Load results

merged <- qread("/work/proteomics/02_data/03_objects/concurrency.qs")
pd_data <- merged %>% filter(comparison == "CTRL vs PD")

pd_interesting <- pd_data %>%
  filter(concurrency > 0.6, abs(estimate) > 1, p.value < 0.05) %>%
  arrange(desc(abs(estimate)))

p1 <- ggplot(pd_data, aes(x = concurrency, y = estimate)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  geom_point(data = pd_interesting, color = "red", size = 3) +
  geom_text(data = pd_interesting, aes(label = protein), vjust = -1, size = 3) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(
    title = "Concurrency vs Disease Effect (CTRL vs PD)",
    x = "Concurrency Score",
    y = "Effect Size (CTRL vs PD)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

msa_data <- merged %>% filter(comparison == "CTRL vs MSA")

msa_interesting <- msa_data %>%
  filter(concurrency > 0.6, abs(estimate) > 1, p.value < 0.05) %>%
  arrange(desc(abs(estimate)))

p2 <- ggplot(msa_data, aes(x = concurrency, y = estimate)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  geom_point(data = msa_interesting, color = "red", size = 3) +
  geom_text(data = msa_interesting, aes(label = protein), vjust = -1, size = 3) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(
    title = "Concurrency vs Disease Effect (CTRL vs MSA)",
    x = "Concurrency Score",
    y = "Effect Size (CTRL vs MSA)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

psp_data <- merged %>% filter(comparison == "CTRL vs PSP")

psp_interesting <- psp_data %>%
  filter(concurrency > 0.6, abs(estimate) > 1, p.value < 0.05) %>%
  arrange(desc(abs(estimate)))

p3 <- ggplot(psp_data, aes(x = concurrency, y = estimate)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  geom_point(data = psp_interesting, color = "red", size = 3) +
  geom_text(data = psp_interesting, aes(label = protein), vjust = -1, size = 3) +

    title = "Concurrency vs Disease Effect (CTRL vs PSP)",

cowplot::plot_grid(plotlist = list(p1, p2, p3), nrow = 1)

  unlist() %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>%
